This was about my 5th visit to this establishment. I love it here especially with the beautiful view of the Hudson River. The prices of the beer are great with a great selection. (They also have a small selection of wine!) The food is always good and you can't beat the affordable prices! My only complaint is that the bathroom is unisex but there isn't a door.. So I guess that's better? But not a deal-breaker, all in all great prices, good food, some board games and large TVs to watch sports. PS.. if you have a birthday and request a sparkler then its a additional $2. I found that out by looking at my receipt but good thing I can afford that! Lol. (But please do better with the music! It's always bad lmao) and way too loud!
Had a good time, good company, drinks were definitely on point
Enjoy packed spot

Great place to have fun for happy hour or an evening out on a date or just hanging with friends. The food and drink menu is more then reasonable in terms of pricing. The food was great, I personally had the wings and an order of fries. While waiting the waiter brought us over UNO cards for the table to play. They have other games there for groups to have fun with like jenga and connect four. All of us had a blast and will be returning again. Highly recommended. Adults only too. Kids have to go up to Dinosaur BBQ. Overall great fun, you won't be disappointed

We had confirmed reservations for Bierstrasse and they failed to open. We walked here and had the greatest time. They were able to accommodate the 22+ family members and did it well. The food and drinks were on point and our server was the sweetest. I will return and I live in Queens.

I felt the customer service was lousy especially for a large group with rsvp. We stress the importance of the event. Also, we couldn't play several games because they were too close to each other. Food was okay. Bartender wasn't aware how to make a cosmopolitan.
123BSB is cool, finger foods are really good and wont break the bank, everything is very well priced, good selection of beers and are always cold and right by the water.
Affordably priced drinks, great location, friendly staff!  There’s a reason I keep coming back.

She answered any questions I had and the food was really good (and that’s says a lot about “bar food”). Super convenient that they are also open until 4 am!! Definitely will be back for their grand opening on the 7th. I’d advise you to come too!

I was walking the West Harlem Pier and discovered 123 BSB on 125th. First off great location. The ambaunce was well design to fit the entire sport bar theme with a modern touch. The food and drinks are very affordable and the staff is wonderful. I highly recommend anyone to visit the location to see what it have to offer. Awesome location and view.

I visited this establishment late night on a Sunday. It was quite but I can definitely see this place being the hot new hangout for a Friday and Saturday night. Capri took care of me. She was attentive and always had a smile. I order the waffle fries and fried ravioli. Both were exactly what I needed. I usually don't eat fried food but this was worth it. The side of waffle fries was big enough to share. Prices are Great. Establishment is brand new and beautiful. Very Clean. I'll definitely come back and rent the games for a fun night with friends. The menu says it's $2 per game.

The sliders and the ribs are specifically delicious, and the servers are friendly and understanding. The beer selection was out of this world. I would definitely recommend this restaurant for a great place to watch a game and eat some great food!
